
0) Test templates in ptfs/chem (DONE)

1) Add a SolverTmp class to the hierarchy.  One Solver per 
   block, two propagators per solver.

2) Build a simple 1D finite difference code.
   Use directory fd1d, namespace Fd1d.
   Use simple relaxation and Newton-Raphson iterators.

   System {
      Mixture
      Boundary
      Interaction
      Iterator
   }

3) Build a pseudospectral code for 1D periodic functions.
   Use directory ps1d, namespace Ps1d

   System {
      Mixture
      Boundary
      SpaceGroup
      Basis
      Interaction
      Iterator
   }

   Start with RelaxationIterator and NewtonRaphsonIterator

4) Generalize periodic code to 2D and 3D, via templates if possible.

5) Add code for symmetry adapted basis functions.

6) Add approximate NR Iterator, AndersonIterator.

7) Add stress calculators.
